description.narrative: The National Children Commission Bill was passed by Parliament and assented to by the President in April. This represents a significant milestone for children's rights in Malawi with the law enabling the establishment of a Commission to facilitate multi-sectoral coordination of children's issues and programs across ministries and departments to ensure implementation of children's rights. UNICEF's strategic budget advocacy has resulted in notable increases in budget allocations to interventions that matter for the well-being of children such as immunization and social cash transfers. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
